    "In the combined dataset we identified hepatocytes, endothelial cells (EC), cholangiocytes, immune cells, and mesenchymal cells as the major cell types (Fig. 2d and Supplementary Fig.",
    "5), recovered in similar proportions from all donors and conditions (Fig. 2e and Supplementary Fig.",
    "For each cell type we compared gene expression levels in post-PVE conditions to their counterparts in healthy liver tissue.",
    "DE genes in all cell types except hepatocytes were more often upregulated in both regenerating and embolized conditions (Fig. 2f, Supplementary Data 4).",
    "Such regeneration kinetics are consistent with previous results showing that hepatocytes are the first cell types entering the regeneration program after hepatectomy, and are followed by cell types responsible for tissue reorganization, including liver vasculature and bile ducts reestablishment 26, 27."
